Male (from Canarana; 
MPEG
022624
):

Eye arrangement as is female, ALE on discrete ocular mounds. Prosoma granulated, predominantly orange, darker at sides and median region (
Figs 9A, B
). Sternum orange with darker borders, labium endites and chelicerae reddish-brown. Clypeus orange with two diagonal darker taints (
Fig. 9B
). Opisthosoma light yellow, with discrete lateral projections, similar with those of males of 

E. dimidiaster


sp. nov.

and 

E. taczanowskii

. Legs with orange femora, tibiae, tarsi and metatarsi; patellae yellow. Palpi with discoid tegulum, RTA long, acute and with margins bended, DTA pointed retrolaterally with tip directed upwards (
Fig. 9D
); TF emerging from tegulum at ten o’clock position (
Fig. 9C
).

Distribution. BRAZIL : São Paulo , Minas Gerais , Espírito Santo , Mato Grosso , Bahia , Acre , Rondônia , Amazonas , Pará ;
PANAMA
: Colón ( Fig. 17B ).
